        "client_msg_id": "2b66a006-de68-4c40-9730-a4f4a50e205a",
        "text": "&gt; I'm terrified that our craft will die, and nobody will even care to mourn it.\nI agree with Tudor _and_ this sentence. I enjoy software as a craft, but moments like these are revelatory because they always reveal what we as a whole _actually_ value.\n\nIt's possible that an increase in slop will increase the value of crafted, intentional experiences (not just even in software, but in general) but I'm not sure I'm optimistic.\n\nReally, I'm more curious where this takes us as a species. When we outsource everything and care diminishes, what's left? Do we move to bigger and better concerns? Or do we atrophy? At what point do we become a species left with a bunch of opaque magical artifacts that we don't understand?",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "2eda45ee6ebb",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2025-10-17\/9715127743859_2eda45ee6ebb6dcdb749_72.png",
            "first_name": "Matt",
            "real_name": "Matt Curtis",
            "display_name": "",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "matt.curtis.biz",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1770699204.155279",
        "parent_user_id": "U06NSFX5119",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "3GL1Z",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "I'm terrified that our craft will die, and nobody will even care to mourn it."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "I agree with Tudor "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "and ",
                                "style": {
                                    "italic": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "this sentence. I enjoy software as a craft, but moments like these are revelatory because they always reveal what we as a whole "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "actually",
                                "style": {
                                    "italic": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " value.\n\nIt's possible that an increase in slop will increase the value of crafted, intentional experiences (not just even in software, but in general) but I'm not sure I'm optimistic.\n\nReally, I'm more curious where this takes us as a species. When we outsource everything and care diminishes, what's left? Do we move to bigger and better concerns? Or do we atrophy? At what point do we become a species left with a bunch of opaque magical artifacts that we don't understand?"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
